4Ô∏è‚É£ Formal Finding Documentation

üìÑ Finding Title
Weak Password Policy Enables Credential Attacks

Severity: Critical

Description
The Active Directory domain password policy is severely misconfigured. Password complexity is disabled, minimum password length is set to 5 characters, password expiration is not enforced, and account lockout thresholds are disabled. Additionally, password policy information is accessible through unauthenticated or low-privileged SMB enumeration.

Risk:
These weaknesses allow attackers to:

1.Perform unlimited brute-force attacks
2.Conduct effective password spraying
3.Reuse compromised credentials indefinitely
4.Escalate privileges and move laterally across the domain
5.This significantly lowers the effort required for full domain compromise.


Recommendation:

1.Enforce minimum password length of 14 characters
2.Enable password complexity requirements
3.Configure password history (‚â• 24)
4.Set password expiration to ‚â§ 90 days
5.Enable account lockout after 5 failed attempts
6.Restrict anonymous SMB enumeration
7.Implement MFA for privileged accounts

Business Impact
Failure to remediate may result in:

1.Credential theft
2.Unauthorized access
3.Data breaches
4.Full domain compromise
